            <h2>Cannabis Law Overview in Australia</h2>
            <p>The question "is weed legal in Australia?" doesn't have a simple yes or no answer. Cannabis laws in Australia are complex, varying between federal and state/territory legislation.</p>
            
            <p>At the federal level, cannabis is classified as a Schedule 9 prohibited substance under the Poisons Standard. However, medical cannabis products are classified as Schedule 8 (controlled drugs) or Schedule 4 (prescription medicines), making them legal with a valid prescription.</p>

            <h3>Key Points About Australian Weed Laws:</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Recreational use</strong> is illegal in all states except ACT (decriminalized)</li>
              <li><strong>Medical cannabis</strong> has been legal nationwide since 2016</li>
              <li><strong>Personal cultivation</strong> is only legal in ACT (up to 2 plants)</li>
              <li><strong>CBD oil</strong> with less than 0.3% THC is available over-the-counter</li>
              <li><strong>Hemp foods</strong> containing no THC are legal to buy and consume</li>
            </ul>
